  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nCurrently Prysm allows for both snappy compressed and regular ssz encoded messages via p2p. Our security audit concluded allowing these two options is a security risk that can result in a network partition of someone operates nodes without snappy and others operate nodes with snappy enabled. Is there still a need for non-snappy encoded messages in the networking spec, or should the spec enforce snappy-compressed only?",
